What you need to know:  Omanyala said that his only goal when he landed in Mauritius was to win the Africa title after having set a new African record at the Kip Kieno Classic last year with a time of 9.85 seconds.“No African has ever won a medal at the World Championships but it can be achieved now,” said Omanyala, who turned his focus to the World Athletics Championships and Commonwealth Games trials from June 24 to 25 at the Moi International Sports Centre, Kasarani.